{"title_page": "32nd AVN Awards", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number = 32\n| award = [[AVN Award]]s\n| image = 2015 AVN Awards Show Logo.jpeg\n| caption = \n| date = {{Start date|2015|01|24}}<ref name=2015Trophy/>\n| site = [[The Joint (music venue)|The Joint]]<br>[[Hard Rock Hotel and Casino (Las Vegas)|Hard Rock Hotel and Casino]], [[Paradise, Nevada]], USA\n| host = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Alexis Texas]]<ref name=2015Trophy/>\n* [[Tommy Pistol]]<ref name=2015Trophy/>\n* Danielle Stewart<ref name=co-host />\n}}\n| preshow = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Joanna Angel]]<ref name=preshow>{{cite magazine|title=AVN Announces Behind-the-Scenes Hosts for 2015 Awards Show|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Announces-Behind-the-Scenes-Hosts-for-2015-Awards-Show-584048.html|magazine=Adult Video News|accessdate=January 17, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Dana DeArmond]]<ref name=preshow />\n* Karlie Montana<ref name=preshow />\n}}\n| producer = \n| director = \n| best_picture = ''24 XXX: An Axel Braun Parody''<ref name=\"AVNAwardsLiveTweet\" />\n| most_wins = \n| most_nominations = ''Aftermath'' (22)<ref name=\"iafd-blog-intro\" />\n| network = \n| duration = \n| ratings = \n| last = [[31st AVN Awards|31st]]\n| next =  [[33rd AVN Awards|33rd]]\n}}\n\n'''32nd AVN Awards''' was an event during which [[Adult Video News]] (AVN) presented its annual [[AVN Award]]s to honor the best [[Pornographic film|pornographic movies]] and adult entertainment products of 2014 in the [[United States]].<ref name=2015Trophy>{{cite magazine|title=Carmen Caliente, Jillian Janson Named 2015 AVN Awards Trophy Girls New performers selected via social media for coveted honor|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/Carmen-Caliente-Jillian-Janson-Named-2015-AVN-Awards-Trophy-Girls-579896.html|magazine=Adult Video News|accessdate=November 11, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe ceremony was held on January 24, 2015, at [[The Joint (music venue)|The Joint]] in the [[Hard Rock Hotel and Casino (Las Vegas)|Hard Rock Hotel and Casino]], [[Paradise, Nevada]].\n\n''24 XXX: An Axel Braun Parody'' won Best Parody, Best Screenplay-Parody, and Movie of the Year, with [[Axel Braun]] also winning Best Director-Parody, while ''Aftermath'', which had the most nominations of any movie, won Best Drama, Best Screenplay, and Armstrong took home Best Director-Feature. The coveted Best New Starlet and Female Performer of the Year awards went to [[Carter Cruise]] and [[Anikka Albrite]] respectively. Albrite's husband, [[Mick Blue]], won the Male Performer of the Year title.<ref name=\"AVNwinners\">{{cite web|title=2015 AVN Awards Deliver Husband-Wife Performers of the Year|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/2015-AVN-Awards-Deliver-Husband-Wife-Performers-of-the-Year-586073.html|author=Mark Kernes|website=AVN.com|publisher=Adult Video News|accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"AVNwinnerslist\">{{cite web|title=AVN Announces the Winners of the 2015 AVN Awards|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Announces-the-Winners-of-the-2015-AVN-Awards-585973.html|website=AVN.com|publisher=Adult Video News|accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref> This marks the first time in the show's history that a married couple has simultaneously won both Performer of the Year awards.<ref>{{cite magazine|url= http://business.avn.com/articles/video/Blue-Albrite-Star-in-Mainstream-Austrian-Movie-588015.html|title= Blue, Albrite Star in Mainstream Austrian Movie|accessdate= February 6, 2015|author= Peter Warren|date= February 5, 2015|magazine= [[AVN (magazine)|AVN]]}}</ref>\n\nThe ''[[International Business Times]]'' found \"a surprise: The Best Non-Feature Film award went to a female director, [[Mason (director)|Mason]], for ''Allie'', although she was a no-show at the ceremony she also won Director of the Year.\n\nA video featuring [[Tila Tequila]] won the award for Best Celebrity Sex Tape over videos featuring [[Farrah Abraham]] and [[Mimi Faust]].<ref name=\"AVNwinnerslist\" /><ref name=\"Celebwinners\">{{cite web|title=Tila Tequila Wins AVN Award For Best Celebrity Sex Tape Over Farrah Abraham And Mima Faust|url=http://popdust.com/2015/01/25/best-celebrity-sexy-tape-avn/|website=Popdust.com|publisher=Popdust Inc.|accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe awards show was recorded for its annual national broadcast on cable TV in the United States in mid-2015.<ref name=\"co-host\" />\n\n==Winners and nominees==\nOn August 27, 2014, the award categories for the 2015 ceremonies were announced. A change to the categories was announced in that VOD-only titles would be accepted according to certain eligibility requirements.<ref name=AVNcats>{{cite magazine|title=AVN Media Network Announces Categories for 2015 AVN Awards|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Media-Network-Announces-Categories-for-2015-AVN-Awards-570997.html|magazine=Adult Video News|accessdate=November 11, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn November 20, 2014, the nominees for the 2015 awards were announced at an event in [[Hollywood]] which represented the first time that [[AVN Media Network]] had announced its nominees at a public event. According to the AVN staff, \"AVN streamlined the categories for the 2015 AVN Awards with the aim of making it easier for studios, [[Film director|directors]] and performers to find the correct ways in which to nominate their work. Some redundancies were eliminated and categories that were too similar were in some cases merged together to create a tight list of 108 categories.\"<ref name=2015Nominees>{{cite magazine|title=Nominations for 2015 AVN Awards Released|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/Nominations-for-2015-AVN-Awards-Released-581008.html|magazine=Adult Video News|accessdate=November 23, 2014}}</ref><ref name=2015Noms>{{cite web|title=2015 AVN Award Nominees |url=http://avnawards.avn.com/pages/4 |website=AVN.com |publisher=Adult Video News |accessdate=November 23, 2014 |url-status=dead  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141230202705/http://avnawards.avn.com/pages/4 |archivedate=December 30, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n===Major awards===\n[[File:Anikka_Albrite_2015.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Anikka Albrite]], winner of the 2015 [[AVN Female Performer of the Year Award]]]]\n[[File:Mick_Blue_2015.jpg|thumb|right|150px|[[Mick Blue]], winner of the 2015 AVN [[AVN Award for Male Performer of the Year|Male Performer of the Year Award]]]]\n[[File:Carter Cruise 2015.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Carter Cruise]], winner of the 2015 AVN Best New Starlet & Best Actress]]\n[[File:Venus Lux 2015.jpg|thumb|150px|[[Venus Lux]], winner of the 2015 AVN Transsexual Performer of the Year Award]]\n[[File:Steven_St._Croix_2013.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Steven St. Croix]], winner of the 2015 AVN [[AVN Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] Award]]\n\nWinners of categories (listed in reverse order of presentation) announced during the awards ceremony January 24, 2015, are highlighted in '''boldface'''.<ref name=\"AVNAwardsLiveTweet\">{{cite magazine|title=AVN Awards 2015 Twitter feed|url=https://twitter.com/avnawards|magazine=Adult Video News|accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref><ref name=AVNwinnerslist />\n\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! style=\"background:#89cff0; width:50%\" | Movie of the Year\n! style=\"background:#89cff0; width:50%\" | Transsexual Performer of the Year\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''''24 XXX: An Axel Braun Parody''''' (Best Parody)'''<ref name=\"AVNAwardsLiveTweet\" /><ref name=AVNwinnerslist />\n(Rather than nominees for this category, contenders are chosen from the winners in the \"Best Release\" categories such as Best Vignette Release, Best Parody Release and several others. Voting is conducted separately just prior to the awards ceremony.)<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Unveils-First-Ever-Movie-of-the-Year-Award-459634.html |title=AVN Unveils First-Ever Movie of the Year Award|magazine=Adult Video News|date=January 11, 2012|accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref>\n| valign=\"top\"