[[List of members of the AVN Hall of Fame]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|33em}}\n\n== References ==\n{{cite AV media\n | people = Gary D. Miller (Director)\n | year = 2012\n | title = The 2012 AVN Awards Show\n |trans-title=| medium = Television production\n | url =\n | accessdate =\n | archiveurl =\n | archivedate =\n | format =\n | time =\n | publisher = Showtime Networks\n | location = Los Angeles, California\n | id =\n | isbn =\n | oclc =\n | quote =\n | ref =\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category|AVN Awards 2012}}\n\n* [http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Announces-the-2012-AVN-Award-Winners-461715.html \"AVN Announces the 2012 AVN Award Winners\"]\n* AVN Awards Nominees:\n**[https://web.archive.org/web/20120131034635/http://avnawards.avn.com/2012_AVN_Awards_nominations.pdf 2012] (archived at [[Digital time capsule|Wayback Machine]], January 2, 2012)\n**[http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Awards-2012-The-Nominees-456084.html AVN Awards 2012: The Nominees - click near \"downloaded as a pdf file by clicking here.\"]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/Sections/Awards/Adult_Video_News_Awards/ Adult Video News Awards] at the [[Internet Movie Database]]\n* {{IMDb title | 2335496 | 2012 AVN Awards Show | (2012 TV Special) }}\n\n{{AVN}}\n\n[[Category:AVN Awards]]\n[[Category:Hard Rock Hotel and Casino (Las Vegas)|AVN Awards 29]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number = 29\n| award = [[AVN Award]]s\n| image = 29th_Adult_Video_News_Awards_2012_logo.jpg\n| caption = \n| date = {{Start date|2012|01|21}}\n| site = [[The Joint (music venue)|The Joint]]<br>[[Hard Rock Hotel and Casino (Las Vegas)|Hard Rock Hotel and Casino]], [[Paradise, Nevada|Paradise]], [[Nevada]]\n| host = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Dave Attell]]<ref name=autogenerated1>{{citation|date=August 2012|title=Rock Hard at the Hard Rock|journal=Cheri Magazine|issue=191 |publisher=Berkeley Publications|publication-place=Paramus, New Jersey|pages=94\u2013101|issn=1059-7131 |oclc=24682494 |quote=Hosted by comedian Dave Attell, he joked 'This is a sexy hotel, man; they sell lubricant in the gift shop...'}}</ref>\n* [[Bree Olson]]\n* [[Sunny Leone]]\n}}\n| preshow = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Jesse Jane]]\n* [[Kirsten Price (actress)|Kirsten Price]]\n* [[Dave Navarro]]\n* [[Kayden Kross]]\n* [[Jessie Andrews]]\n}}\n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n* Gary D. Miller\n* Eric Mittleman\n}}\n| director = Gary D. Miller\n| best_picture = ''[[Portrait of a Call Girl]]''\n| most_wins = ''The Rocki Whore Picture Show: A Hardcore Parody'' (9)\n| most_nominations = ''The Rocki Whore Picture Show: A Hardcore Parody'' (18)\n| network = [[Showtime (TV channel)|Showtime]]\n| duration = 1 hour, 50 minutes\n| ratings = \n| last = [[28th AVN Awards|28th]]\n| next = [[30th AVN Awards|30th]]\n}}\n\nThe '''29th AVN Awards''' ceremony, presented by ''[[Adult Video News]]'', honored the best [[pornographic movies]] and adult entertainment products of 2011 of the [[United States]] and took place January 21, 2012, at a new venue, [[The Joint (music venue)|The Joint]] inside the [[Hard Rock Hotel and Casino (Las Vegas)|Hard Rock Hotel and Casino]] in [[Paradise, Nevada]]. Movies or products released between Oct. 1, 2010 and Sept. 30, 2011 were eligible. The ceremony was televised in the United States by [[Showtime (TV channel)|Showtime]]. Comedian [[Dave Attell]] hosted the show<ref name=autogenerated1 /> for the second time. He first presided over the [[27th AVN Awards|27th ceremony]] held in 2010, and shared the 29th ceremony with co-hosts [[Bree Olson]] and [[Sunny Leone]]. The awards show was held together with the [[Adult Entertainment Expo]] and Internext at the same venue.\n\nOn January 11, 2012, AVN announced in a press release that for the first time the AVN Awards ceremony would climax with \"the presentation of an all-encompassing grand accolade,\" Movie of the Year. \"Even since the beginning, when we presented separate awards for Best Film and Best Video Feature, there's been no definitive AVN Award equivalent to Best Picture. Now we have one,\" said AVN senior editor Peter Warren. Rather than nominees, contenders would be chosen from the winners in the categories of: Best All-Sex Release, Best All-Sex Release \u2013 Mixed Format, Best All-Girl Release, Best Gonzo Release, Best Vignette Release, Best Comedy, Best Feature, Best Foreign Feature, Best Parody \u2013 Comedy and Best Parody \u2013 Drama. Voting for Movie of the Year would be conducted just prior to the January 21 ceremony, in a secret meeting of core members of the AVN Awards committee, to ensure winners of the 10 categories remain secret until their presentation.<ref>{{cite press release | url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Unveils-First-Ever-Movie-of-the-Year-Award-459634.html | title=AVN Unveils First-Ever Movie of the Year Award | publisher=Adult Video News | date=January 11, 2012 | accessdate=January 13, 2013}}</ref> The event would also unveiled a new annual award, the [[#Honorary AVN Awards|Visionary Award]], \"created to recognize and honor a leader in adult entertainment who has propelled innovation and taken his company\u2014and the business as a whole\u2014to new heights.\"<ref>{{cite press release | url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/Steve-Hirsch-to-Receive-First-Visionary-Award-at-AVN-Awards-454298.html | title=Steve Hirsch to Receive First Visionary Award at AVN Awards | publisher=Adult Video News | date=November 10, 2011 | accessdate=January 14, 2013}}</ref>\n\n''The Rocki Whore Picture Show: A Hardcore Parody'' and ''Asa Akira Is Insatiable 2'' won the most awards, nine and seven respectively, but the Movie of the Year award went to ''[[Portrait of a Call Girl]]''. ''Portrait'' also won for Best Feature, Best Actress for [[Jessie Andrews]] and Best Director \u2014 Feature for Graham Travis. ''Rocki Whore'' won Best Director\u2014Parody for [[Brad Armstrong (director)|Brad Armstrong]], Best Screenplay\u2014Parody for Armstrong and Hank Shenanigan and Best Parody \u2014 Comedy, among others. ''Insatiable 2'' won Best All-Sex Release, Best Director \u2014 Non Feature for [[Mason (director)|Mason]] and several best sex scene awards for [[Asa Akira]] and her co-stars. Individually, Akira won or shared six awards, but the coveted [[AVN Female Performer of the Year Award|Female Performer of the Year]] and Best New Starlet awards went to [[Bobbi Starr]] and [[Brooklyn Lee]] respectively. Lee took home five awards on the night and four went to Starr. [[Manuel Ferrara]] won his fourth Male Performer of the Year award, more than anyone else in the event's 29-year history.<ref name=\"avn0312\">Mark Kernes, \"Joint Production\", ''Adult Video News'', Vol. 28, No. 3, March 2012, pp. 44\u201358.</ref>\n\n== Winners and nominees ==\n[[File:Bobbi Starr 2010.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Bobbi Starr]], Female Performer of the Year winner]]\n[[File:Manuel Ferrara 2010.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Manuel Ferrara]], [[AVN Award for Male Performer of the Year|Male Performer of the Year]] winner]]\n[[File:Brooklyn Lee 2013.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Brooklyn Lee]], Best New Starlet winner]]\n[[File:Jessie Andrews 2014.jpg|right|thumb|150px|[[Jessie Andrews]], Best Actress winner]]\n[[File:Dale DaBone 2010.jpg|right|thumb|150px|\n[[Dale DaBone]], [[AVN Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] winner]]\n\nThe nominees for the 29th AVN Awards were announced on Dec. 6, 2011 in a press release.Those nominees were Gary Kirker from Las Cruces, New Mexico. ref name=\"nominees\">{{cite press release | url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Awards-2012-The-Nominees-456084.html | title=AVN Awards 2012: The Nominees | publisher=Adult Video News | date=December 6, 2011 | accessdate=January 13, 2013}}</ref> The film receiving the most nominations was ''The Rocki Whore Picture Show: A Hardcore Parody'' with 18, while performer/director Bobbi Starr had the most individual nominations with 16. The winners were announced during the awards ceremony on January 21, 2012.\n\n=== Major Awards ===\nThe first AVN Movie of the Year Award went to ''[[Portrait of a Call Girl]]'',<ref name=\"avn0312\" /> which qualified for consideration by winning Best Feature. The other movies in the running were: ''Asa Akira Is Insatiable 2'' (Best All-Sex Release), ''Bobbi\u2019s World'' (Best All-Sex Release \u2013 Mixed Format), ''Cherry 2'' (Best All-Girl Release), ''Dangerous Curves'' (Best Gonzo Release), ''Prison Girls'' (Best Vignette Release), ''Grindhouse XXX'' (Best Comedy), ''Mission Asspossible'' (Best Foreign Feature), ''The Rocki Whore Picture Show: A Hardcore Parody'' (Best Parody \u2013 Comedy) and ''[[Vivid Superhero|Spider-Man XXX: A Porn Parody]]'' (Best Parody \u2013 Drama).\n\nAdditional major awards are listed below with winner first and highlighted in '''boldface''' followed by the rest of the nominees.\n\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! style=\"background:#89cff0; width:50%\" | [[AVN Award for Male Performer of the Year|Male Performer of the Year]]\n! style=\"background:#89cff0; width:50%\" | [[AVN Female Performer of the Year Award|Female Performer of the Year]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''[[Manuel Ferrara]]'''\n** [[Mick Blue]]\n** [[Tom Byron]]\n** [[James Deen]]\n** [[Erik Everhard]]\n** [[Tommy Gunn (pornographic actor)|Tommy Gunn]]\n** [[Keiran Lee]]\n** [[Ram\u00f3n Nomar]]\n** [[Mr. Pete]]\n** [[Rocco Reed]]\n** Anthony Rosano\n** [[Lexington Steele]]\n** [[Evan Stone]]\n** [[Nacho Vidal]]\n** [[Prince Yahshua]]\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''[[Bobbi Starr]]'''\n** [[Asa Akira]]\n** [[Lexi Belle]]\n** [[Dana DeArmond]]\n** Gracie Glam\n** Allie Haze\n** [[Jesse Jane]]\n** [[Kagney Linn Karter]]\n** [[Kimberly Kane]]\n** [[Kayden Kross]]\n** Lily Labeau\n** Phoenix Marie\n** [[Chanel Preston]]\n** Kristina Rose\n** Andy San Dimas\n** [[Alexis Texas]]\n|-\n! style=\"background:#89cff0\" | Best Male Newcomer\n! style=\"background:#89cff0\" | Best New Starlet\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n* '''[[Xander 