Students\n==Athletics==\nForeman's varsity athletic teams are named the [[Hornet]]s and competes in the [[Chicago Public League]] (CPL) and is a member of the [[Illinois High School Association]] (IHSA). The boys' basketball team were regional champions two times (2009\u20132010 and 2016\u20132017). In 1999\u20132000, the boys' cross country were Class AA. The boys' soccer team were public league champions one time (1993\u20131994 and 1996\u20131997), regional champions three times (2002\u20132003, 2014\u20132015 and 2015\u20132016) and Class AA one time (2002\u20132003). \nThe Foreman Hornets compete in a variety of fall, winter and spring interscholastic competitive sports administered by the [[Chicago Public High School League]] including;\n* Fall sports: Cheer-leading (Girls), Cross Country (Boys/Girls), Football (Boys), Soccer (Boys), Volleyball (Girls)\n* Winter sports: Basketball (Boys/Girls), Wrestling (Boys) Bowling (Boys/Girls), Cheer-leading (Girls), Swimming (Boys)\n* Spring sports: Baseball (Boys), Soccer (Girls), Softball (Girls), Track (Boys/Girls), Volleyball (Boys), Water-polo (Boys/Girls)\n==Clubs and Activities==\nForeman High School has a number of clubs and activities such as: Academic Decathlon, Aspira, Asian Club, Black Heritage Club, Chess Club, Computer Club, Drama Club, Humanitarian Club, Math Club, [[National Honor Society]], Newspaper, Peer Health Advocates, Photography Club, Polish Club, Scholastic Achievers, Student Council, Student Development Team, and Yearbook.\n==Other Information==\nExterior shots of the school is used in the [[Disney Channel]] family sitcom ''[[Raven's Home]]''.<ref name=RH>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/filming_chicago/status/873035709107519492|title=Finally Sat June 10: Disney is shooting B Roll (no cast!) for Raven's Home (That's So Raven sequel) @ Foreman High 3234 N LeClaire|last=InChicago|first=Filming|website=Twitter.com|access-date=2019-12-31}}</ref>{{cn|date=December 2019}}\n==Notable people ==\nThe following are notable people associated with Foreman High School. If the person was a Foreman High School student, the number in parentheses indicates the year of graduation; if the person was a faculty or staff member, that person's title and years of association are included.\n* [[Rod Blagojevich]] \u2014 (1974), politician; former [[Illinois]] [[governor]].\n* [[Peter Francis Geraci]] \u2014 (attended), [[Chicago]]-based [[bankruptcy]] [[lawyer|attorney]].\n* [[Bernita Hampton]] \u2014 (1985), Extraordinary Mother of Lauren and [[Julian Rhodes]] ; Died. 2017 [[Illinois]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.foremanhs.org}}\n* [http://www.cps.edu/Schools/Pages/school.aspx?id=609708 Chicago Public Schools: Foreman]\n{{Chicago Public Schools}}\n{{Chicago Public League}}\n\n[[Category:Chicago Public Schools]]\n[[Category:Public high schools in Chicago]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1928]]\n\n\n{{Illinois-school-stub}}\n{{Chicago-struct-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Jkerbis", "label": "safe", "comment": "added one name to notable alumni (Gertrude Lempp Kerbis)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foreman_High_School_(Chicago)"}
{"title_page": "25th AVN Awards", "text_new": "{{Infobox film awards\n| number = 25\n| award = [[AVN Award]]s\n| image = 25th AVN Awards.jpg\n| image_border = \n| size = \n| caption = <small>[[Tera Patrick]] on the event's poster.</small>\n| date = {{Start date|2008|01|12}}<ref>{{cite web|title=The 2008 AVN Adult Movie Awards Show|url=http://www.thefloatingworld.com/avnwards-January-12-2008.html|publisher=The Floating World|accessdate=16 April 2015}}</ref>\n| site = [[Mandalay Bay Events Center]]<br>[[Paradise, Nevada]], USA\n| host = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Tera Patrick]]<ref name=tera>{{cite magazine|title=Tera Patrick Named 2008 AVN Awards Host|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=86208&mi=all&q=2008+avn|magazine=Adult Video News|accessdate=16 April 2015|date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304072750/http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=86208&mi=all&q=2008+avn|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* [[Greg Fitzsimmons]]<ref name=\"2008winners\"/>\n}}\n| preshow =\n| producer = \n| director = \n| best_picture = ''Layout''<ref name=vivid>{{cite magazine|title=Vivid Entertainment Dominates The 2008 AVN Awards|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=89107&mi=all&q=2008+avn|magazine=Adult Video News|accessdate=16 April 2015|date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304071724/http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=89107&mi=all&q=2008+avn|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| most_wins = \n| most_nominations =\n| network = [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n| duration = \n| ratings = \n| last = [[24th AVN Awards|24th]]\n| next = [[26th AVN Awards|26th]]\n}}\n\n'''''The 25th AVN Awards''''' was an event during which [[Adult Video News]] (AVN) presented its annual [[AVN Awards]] to honor the best [[pornographic film|pornographic movies]] and [[adult entertainment]] products of 2007 in the [[United States]].\n\nThe ceremony was held on January 12, 2008, at the [[Mandalay Bay Events Center]], in [[Paradise, Nevada]].\n\n==Ceremony==\n\nThe 25th Anniversary Adult Video News awards made its broadcast premiere on [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]] on March 14. The two-hour presentation, billed as ''The AVN Adult Movie Awards'', was taped on January 12 at the [[Mandalay Bay Events Center]] in [[Paradise, Nevada]]. For the first time the show was shot on [[High-definition television|High-Definition]] and was also broadcast in that format.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/AVN-Awards-Show-Debuts-27186.html|title=AVN Awards Show Debuts|author=AVN|work=AVN.com|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nAVN announced nominations for its annual awards on November 26, 2007. Nominees in the 114 categories were selected by the AVN staff, and winners were selected by AVN writers and other adult film reviewers.<ref name=nomnews>{{cite web|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=86872&mi=all&q=avn+hall+of+fame|title=AVN Releases Nominations for 2008 Award Show|author=Tod Hunter|work=XBIZ.com|accessdate=April 16, 2015|date=November 26, 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417044528/http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=86872&mi=all&q=avn+hall+of+fame|archive-date=April 17, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nLeaders in nominations were ''Upload'', a [[science-fiction]] [[Thriller (genre)|thriller]] video from SexZ Pictures, with 22 nominations, and ''Layout'', a film from [[Vivid Entertainment]], with 18. This is the last year for separate film and video categories at the AVN awards.<ref name=nomnews/>\n\n[[Performer]]/[[Film director|director]] [[Belladonna (actress)|Belladonna]] received nine nominations, for Best Director (Non-Feature), Director of the Year and seven sex scenes. Performer/director [[Stormy Daniels]] received seven nominations, for acting, directing, screenplay, Director of the Year, Female Performer of the Year, Crossover Star of the Year, and Couples Sex Scene with veteran performer [[Randy Spears]].\n\nSpears himself received five nominations, including Best Actor (Video), Best Supporting Actor (Film) and Male Performer of the Year; performer [[Steven St. Croix]] received five, four for acting and one sex scene; performer/director [[Brad Armstrong (director)|Brad Armstrong]] received four, for acting, screenplay, and two for direction.\n\n[[Wicked Pictures]] and its affiliated companies led the nominations count with 91, followed by [[Evil Angel (studio)|Evil Angel Productions]] and its affiliates with 88, [[Vivid Entertainment]] and its affiliates with 84, Pure Play Media and its affiliates with 48, [[Digital Playground]] and its affiliates with 41, [[JM Productions]] and its affiliates with 39, [[Elegant Angel|Elegant Angel Productions]] with 33, [[Adam & Eve (company)|Adam & Eve Pictures]] and its affiliates with 32 and [[Hustler Video]] and its affiliates with 31.\n\nThis year's additions to the [[AVN Hall of Fame]] are [[performers]] [[Brittany Andrews]], [[Jay Ashley]], [[Angel Kelly]], [[Dyanna Lauren]], [[Raylene]], [[Ruby (actress)|Ruby]], [[Alexandra Silk]], [[Angela Summers]] and [[Tasha Voux]], performer/director [[Skye Blue]], [[cameraman]] Jake Jacobs and director [[Michael Raven]].\n\n===Changes in categories===\nThe 25th annual AVN Awards was the last at which productions shot on film are divided into separate categories from those shot on video. This change comes due to the very few number of companies producing films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/Film-Categories-To-Be-Discontinued-After-2008-AVN-Awards-24883.html|title=Film Categories To Be Discontinued After 2008 AVN Awards|author=AVN|work=AVN.com|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref>\n\nAVN president [[Paul Fishbein]] stated, \"If people make films, they'll be eligible in every category, and if there are enough of them, then we'll have a separate Best Film category.\"\n\nThe AVN Award categories that have until this year been divided up into film and video are: Best Actor, Best Actress, Best All-Girl Sex Scene, Best Anal Sex Scene, Best Art Direction, Best Cinematography/Videography, Best Couples Sex Scene, Best Director, Best Editing, Best Group Sex Scene, Best Oral Sex Scene, Best Screenplay, Best Supporting Actor and Best Supporting Actress.\n\n==Main awards==\nWinners of categories announced during the awards ceremony November 30, 2008, are highlighted in boldface.<ref name=\"2008winners\">{{cite web|url=http://www.avn.com/video/articles/2759.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080404082611/http://www.avn.com/video/articles/2759.html|archivedate=2008-04-04|title=2008 AVN Awards Winners Announced|author=Jared Rutter|work=AVN.com|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref><ref name=winners>{{cite web|url=http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=88772&mi=all&q=2008+avn|title=AVN Announces 2008 Adult Movie Awards Winners|author=Steve Javors|work=Xbiz.com|accessdate=17 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150417010452/http://www.xbiz.com/news/news_piece.php?id=88772&mi=all&q=2008+avn|archive-date=17 April 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=nominations>{{cite web|url=http://www.avnawards.com/pdf/2008Nominations.pdf|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080227073556/http://www.avnawards.com/pdf/2008Nominations.pdf|archivedate=2008-02-27|title=The 2008 AVN Awards Nominations|author=AVN|work=AVN.com|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref>\n[[File:Evan Stone AVN Adult Entertainment Expo 2010.jpg|thumb|right|225px|[[Evan Stone]] winner of [[AVN Award for Male Performer of the Year|Male Performer of the Year]]]]\n[[File:Sasha Grey EXXXOTICA 2008.jpg|thumb|right|225px|[[Sasha Grey]] winner of Performer of the Year]]\n[[File:Eva Angelina3 adjusted.jpg|thumb|right|225px|[[Eva Angelina]] won Best Actress Video for ''Upload'']]\n[[File:Penny Flame at AVN Adult Entertainment Expo 2008.jpg|thumb|right|225px|[[Penny Flame]] won Best Actress Film for ''Layout'']]\n[[File:Bree Olson 20080110 Adult Entertainment Expo 2.jpg|thumb|right|225px|[